ried works that make up his oeuvre. Upon the imminent publication of the second edition of Either/Or, Kierkegaard again intended to cease writing. Now was the time for a direct "report to history" on the authorship as a whole. In addition to Point of View, which was published posthumously, the present volume also contains On My Work as an Author, a contemporary substitute, and the companion piece Armed Neutrality.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aAuthors, DanishzDenmarkvBiography. 0aChristian lifexLutheran authors. 0aDeathxReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aGod (Christianity)xWorship and love. 0aMarriagexReligious aspectsxChristianity. 0aPhilosopherszDenmarkvBiography. 0aTheologianszDenmarkvBiography. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Religious.2bisacsh1 aHong, Edna H., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHong, Howard V., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999z978311044249640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978140083240840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781400832408423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781400832408.jpg  a978-3-11-044249-6  Princeton University Press eBook-Package Archive 1927-1999c1927d1999  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_PLTLJSIS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK